article.headline: New Orleans 80, Louisiana-Lafayette 76
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Bo McCalebb scored a career-high 36 points as New Orleans opened its Sun Belt Conference season with an 80-76 win over Louisiana-Lafayette on Wednesday. McCalebb was 12-of-20 from the field and 10-of-12 from the free throw line to help the Privateers (4-6, 1-0 SBC) win their conference opener for the fourth time in five seasons. Jamie McNeilly added 18 points, and New Orleans committed a season-low six turnovers in snapping a five-game losing streak to Louisiana-Lafayette (2-7, 0-1 SBC). David Dees had 18 points on 6-of-16 shooting to lead the Ragin' Cajuns, while Ross Mouton tallied 15 points. The Cajuns outrebounded New Orleans 44-26 but struggled to shoot just 37 percent in the second half. Louisiana-Lafayette made 11 of its first 14 shots to take a 29-26 lead in the game's first 10 minutes. The Cajuns shot 63 percent for the half and outrebounded New Orleans 18-8. But McCalebb answered with 22 first-half points, and the Privateers committed just two turnovers as the teams were tied 43-43 at the half.
